gomodel:SYNGO_4114  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 7A: Immunoprecipitation studies indicate that NR2C coprecipitates with SNX27.\nFig 7B: Immunocytochemistry in primary cerebellar neurons shows that SNX27 colocalises with NR2C.\nFig 8A: Immunoblot analysis shows that the level of NR2C was increased by about 35 to 40% in the SNX27-/- brain compared to the wild-type brain.\nFig 8B: Real-time PCR demonstrated that the mRNA levels of NR2C transcripts in brain tissues from wild-type and knockout mice were not significantly different.\nFig 8D: Primary cortical neurons from SNX27+/+ and SNX27-/- mice were transfected with Myc-NR2C and pulse-chased with the anti-Myc antibody for various periods. 85% more NR2C was endocytosed in SNX27+/+ than in SNX27-/- neurons as evidenced by the greater number of internalized NR2C (red puncta) in SNX27+/+ neurons at 5 and 15 min after pulse-chase than in wild-type neurons.. Experimental description: Generation of SNX27-/- mice was performed as described in PMID: 15363411." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4114" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

